---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Omar Maaouane Veiga" description="A bit about Omar Maaouane Veiga — data-driven engineer based in London.">
  <section class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <div class="about-content">
      <p>
        I'm Omar Maaouane Veiga, a London-based engineer with a background in robotics
        and a strong passion for solving problems through data. I enjoy working on
        systems that take in messy, real-world information and turn it into something
        useful, whether that system lives in software, hardware, or somewhere in
        between.
      </p>

      <p>
        My interest in data-driven problem solving started with robotics: building
        systems that took in data and turned it into useful actions.
        Over time, I realised that the same mindset applies incredibly well to data
        analytics, except now I build systems that take in data and turns it into
        useful actions <em>for humans</em>.
      </p>

      <p>
        I’m particularly motivated by work that has real impact. I enjoy building
        tools and analyses that people actually use, that improve decision-making,
        and that make systems more reliable, ethical, or efficient. I’m also deeply
        driven by continuous learning, especially when it pushes me outside my
        comfort zone.
      </p>

      <h2>What I work with</h2>

      <p>
        My work sits at the intersection of engineering and analytics. Depending on
        the problem, that might look like:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Data &amp; Analytics</strong> — Python, data pipelines, exploratory analysis, stakeholder-focused insights</li>
        <li><strong>Software Engineering</strong> — backend systems, APIs, automation, maintainable codebases</li>
        <li><strong>Hardware &amp; Systems</strong> — robotics, embedded systems, sensors, control software</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud &amp; Tooling</strong> — learning and applying modern cloud tools to real problems under tight deadlines</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How I work</h2>

      <p>
        I value clear communication, structured thinking, and collaboration. I’ve
        learned that the best solutions come from understanding stakeholder needs,
        questioning assumptions, and iterating quickly with feedback. I aim to keep
        things simple, robust, and easy to explain — especially when non-technical
        teams rely on the outcome.
      </p>

      <h2>Beyond work</h2>

      <p>
        Outside of engineering, I enjoy tinkering with side projects, exploring ideas
        that spark my curiosity, and learning from communities of people who care
        deeply about what they build. I’m also a long-time origami enthusiast — a
        surprisingly good exercise in patience, precision, and problem solving.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>

      <p>
        I’m always happy to chat about data, engineering, interesting problems, or
        potential collaborations. The best way to reach me is via email or LinkedIn.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

